documentation.text:
@dev Implementation of {Timelock} contract.
 It allows queueing, execution and cancellation of transactions by the
 {admin}. A queued transaction can be executed after the cool-time represented
 by {delay} has elapsed and grace period has not passed since the queuing
 of transaction.
 It allows changing of contract's admin through a queued transaction by the
 prior admin. The new admin the calls {acceptAdmin} to accept its role.

@dev Allows of receiving of ether beforehand or in bulk, so the sending
 ether is optional at the time of tx execution.

documentation.text:
@dev Executes a transaction by making a low level call to its `target`.
 The call reverts if the low-level call made to `target` reverts.
 Requirements:
 - only callable by {admin}
 - tx must already be queued
 - current timestamp is ahead of tx's eta
 - grace period associated with the tx must not have passed
 - the low-level call to tx's `target` must not revert
@dev Gets timestamp from the current block.

devdoc.details: Implementation of {Timelock} contract. It allows queueing, execution and cancellation of transactions by the {admin}. A queued transaction can be executed after the cool-time represented by {delay} has elapsed and grace period has not passed since the queuing of transaction. It allows changing of contract's admin through a queued transaction by the prior admin. The new admin the calls {acceptAdmin} to accept its role.

GRACE_PERIOD().details: Returns the time period a tx is valid for execution after eta has elapsed.

MAXIMUM_DELAY().details: Returns the maxium delay required for execution after a tx is queued

MINIMUM_DELAY().details: Returns the minimum delay required for execution after a tx is queued

acceptAdmin().details: Sets {pendingAdmin} to admin of current contract. A {GovernorAlpha} contract which is already set as {pendingAdmin} of this contract calls this function to set itself as new admin. Requirements: - only callable by {pendingAdmin}

cancelTransaction(address,uint256,string.details: Cancels a transaction by setting its status in {queuedTransactions} mapping. Requirements: - only callable by {admin}

constructor.details: Sets contract's state variable of {admin} and {delay} Requirements: - `admin_` param must not be a zero address - `delay_` param must be within range or min and max delay

executeTransaction(address,uint256,strin.details: Executes a transaction by making a low level call to its `target`. The call reverts if the low-level call made to `target` reverts. Requirements: - only callable by {admin} - tx must already be queued - current timestamp is ahead of tx's eta - grace period associated with the tx must not have passed - the low-level call to tx's `target` must not revert

queueTransaction(address,uint256,string,.details: Queues a transaction by setting its status in {queuedTransactions} mapping. Requirements: - only callable by {admin} - `eta` must lie in future compared to delay referenced from current block

setDelay(uint256).details: Sets the the new value of {delay}. It allows setting of new delay value through queued tx by the admin Requirements: - only current contract can call it - `delay_` param must be within the min and max delay range

setPendingAdmin(address).details: Sets the the new value of {pendingAdmin_}. It allows setting of new pendingAdmin value through queued tx by the admin Requirements: - only current contract can call it
